According to the docs, the [`Card`][1] class does not contain neither `height` nor `width` named parameter.

You can use a `Container` that will have both `height` and `width`:

```
Widget build(BuildContext context) {
  return Center(
    child: Card(
      child: InkWell(
        splashColor: Colors.blue.withAlpha(30),
        onTap: () {
          print(&#39;Card tapped.&#39;);
        },
        child: Container(
          width: 300,
          height: 100,
          child: Text(&#39;A card that can be tapped&#39;),
        ),
      ),
    ),
  );
}
```


  [1]: https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/Card-class.html

